From 1dc4d20f3885c15ff785849dd3217c1cc2f4ecb5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thiraviyam Mariyappan <tmariyap@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Jun 2025 12:09:09 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath12k: DP: enable perf mode and call netif directly

Currently, received packet goes through mac80211 driver which consume
CPU causes low Throughput. So, Introduced the stats disable flag to
decide whether to bypass the the mac80211 driver. With this flag
enable, based on condition check ath12k_dp_rx_check_fast_rx, received
packet directly send to netif_receive_skb and enabled perf_mode to
avoid tx queuing in transmission.

To enable this use below cmd
echo 1 > /sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/pci-0002:01:00.0/stats_disable

Orginal patch:
0337-wifi-ath12k-DP-enable-perf-mode-and-call-netif-direc.patch

Signed-off-by: Thiraviyam Mariyappan <tmariyap@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan S <bselvara@qti.qualcomm.com>
